{"word":"H2860 - חָתָן - châthân - khaw-thawn' - Bridegroom","slug":"H2860","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">חָתָן</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>châthân"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>khaw-thawn'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bridegroom"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D7;&#x05EA;&#x05DF; - cha&#x0302;tha&#x0302;n</b> - <i>khaw-thawn'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H2859\">H2859</a>; a <i>relative</i> by marriage (especially through the bride); figuratively a <i>circumcised</i> child (as a species of religious espousal): - bridegroom, husband, son in law."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2859\">H2859</a>, <a href=\"#/H2861\">H2861</a>"}]}